diff:1658635376:1658635226:=551c551%0a%3c But also I love the "maps" feature from path of exile where for a cost to the player you can open up temporary portals to new but short, preferably shared, experiences.  This can be great for a scheduled play time with friends that you know you won't have to be wasting all your time camping a randomly spawning moband then have to contest it against rivals.  While that experience I just described can be supremely rewarding, itisn't practical for many players.  Having both of these while forcing the player to spend most of their time in the open world, I think is best.%0a---%0a> But also I love the "maps" feature from path of exile where for a cost tothe player you can open up temporary portals to new but short, preferably shared, experiences.%0a
