diff:1658635226:1658382208:=546,556d545%0a%3c %0a%3c !!World%0a%3c %0a%3c I want to use an open world design primarily.  I want the feeling I got in everquest which was high level mobs wrecking noobs and then the noobs get to see high level players coming in and saving them and taking the mob.  I also got this feeling in Celtic Heroes.%0a%3c %0a%3c But also I love the "maps" feature from path of exile where for a cost tothe player you can open up temporary portals to new but short, preferably shared, experiences.%0a%3c %0a%3c The benefit here between this dichotomy is that low and high players will most of the time be in the same areas.  But high players can spend some time away doing exclusive things, but they can't stay there forever.%0a%3c %0a%3c Another benefit is that we can keep the open world content static.  There isnothing worse than taking a break from a game and returning and all the iconicand nostalgic places are now empty, or even worse, significantly different.  With the portal function (instances) we can make those portals different and constantly changing to keep things fresh and exciting, while never loosing the open world nostalgia and consistancy.%0a%3c %0a
