diff:1657668542:1657668447:=367c367%0a%3c You will get the most experience for fighting monsters of your own level but you still can play with others above or below you in level, just a bit less optimally.  This makes sense that from a monster lower level than you, you would learn less than when you were their same level.  But it also can make sense that fighting a monster higher level than you (remember that an average monster of your same level will be as strong as you are), you probably only won because either you got lucky, you were carried by your group, or you were twinked - in which case it makes sense you would learn less.  This is different than any current game I know of and is done to help prevent twinking and power leveling.%0a---%0a> You will get the most experience for fighting monsters of your own level but you still can play with others above or below you in level, just a bit less optimally.  This makes sense that from a monster lower level than you, you would learn less than when you were their same level.  But it also can make sense that fighting a monster higher level than you (remember that an average monster of your same level will be as strong as you are), you probably only won because you got lucky or you were carried by your group, in which case it makes sense you would learn less.  This is different than any current game I know of and is done to help prevent twinking and power leveling.%0a
