author:1657668202=
diff:1657668202:1657668138:=363c363%0a%3c The reason we use the lowest xpm in the group for everyone is to prevent power leveling where a level 5 groups with a level 10 to kill level 5 monsters, making what the level 5 player learned from the fight trivial.  What this also accomplishes is that everyone in the group will level at roughly the same speed together, regardless of what their levels are.  So yes level 1 can play with their level 10 friend and they can both benefit.  They would optimize their xp by fighting monsters halfway between their respective levels, erring to the side of a little higher than halfway.  If anyone in the group is double the monster level or more, no one in the group gets any xp based on the equation. If the xpm comes out negative, then they get zero xp for the encounter.%0a---%0a> The reason we use the lowest xpm in the group for everyone is to prevent power leveling where a level 5 groups with a level 10 to kill level 5 monsters, making what the level 5 player learned from the fight trivial.  What this also accomplishes is that everyone in the group will level at the same speed together, regardless of what their levels are.  So yes level 1 can play with their level 10 friend and they can both benefit.  They would optimize their xp by fighting monsters halfway between their respective levels, erring to the side of a little higher than halfway.  If anyone in the group is double the monster level or more, no one in the group gets any xp based on the equation. If the xpm comes out negative, then they get zero xp for the encounter.%0a
