diff:1657668089:1657667946:=361,363c361%0a%3c You then take this multipler (xpm) and multiply it by the xp of the monster (which is rolled by the blockhash of the killing blow to the monster).  The lowest xp modifier from everyone in the group is what each player in the group has to use to calculate their xp.  Each player will get slightly different xp because their xp roll will be the blockhash concatenated with their NFT to calculate theur exact xp gain from the monster. %0a%3c %0a%3c The reason we use the lowest xpm in the group for everyone is to prevent power leveling where a level 5 groups with a level 10 to kill level 5 monsters, making what the level 5 player learned from the fight trivial.  What this also accomplishes is that everyone in the group will level at the same speed together, regardless of what their levels are.  So yes level 1 can play with their level 10 friend and they can both benefit.  They would optimize their xp by fighting monsters halfway between their respective levels, erring to the side of a little higher than halfway.  If anyone in the group is double the monster level or more, no one in the group gets any xp based on the equation. If the xpm comes out negative, then they get zero xp for the encounter.%0a---%0a> You then take this multipler (xpm) and multiply it by the xp of the monster (which is rolled by the blockhash of the killing blow to the monster).  The lowest xp number from everyone in the group is what each player in the group gets.  This is to prevent power leveling where a level 5 groups with a level 10 to kill level 5 monsters, making what the level 5 player learned from the fight trivial.  What this also accomplishes is that everyone in the group will level at the same speed together, regardless of what their levels are.  So yes level 1 can play with their level 10 friend and they can both benefit.  They would optimize their xp by fighting monsters halfway between their respective levels, erring to the side of a little higher than halfway.  If anyone in the group is double the monster level or more, no one in the group gets any xp based on the equation. If the xpm comes out negative, then they get zero xp for the encounter.%0a
