diff:1657651154:1657649351:=375c375%0a%3c In terms of can someone then bot that character while they are sleeping for example, it would be possible.  One way to counter this would be AI bot recognition blockchain analysis software.  It isn't that these NFT's would be banned if discovered as a bot, you can't remove something valid on the blockchain. But they could be labeled as potential automated accounts (or this account has been traded X# of times) in competing block explorer gui's (a lot like competing browsers, some browsers mark "potentially harmful websites") and items gained by these accounts could also be labeled in gui's, so those who want to play on legit gui's could avoid them.  Also you would be able to see statistics using block explorer GUI for accounts play time and time of day and average play time per day etc to see if they trust this account.%0a---%0a> In terms of can someone then bot that character while they are sleeping for example, it would be possible.  One way to counter this would be AI bot recognition blockchain analysis software.  It isn't that these NFT's would be banned if discovered as a bot, you can't remove something valid on the blockchain. But they could be labeled as potential automated accounts in competing block explorer gui's (a lot like competing browsers, some browsers mark "potentially harmful websites") and items gained by these accounts could also be labeled in gui's, so those who want to play legit could avoid them.  Also you would be able to see statistics using block explorer GUI for accounts play time and time of day and average play time per day etc to see if they trust this account.%0a
