diff:1657638423:1657638385:=371,378d370%0a%3c !!Botting prevention%0a%3c %0a%3c Like has been partially discussed in [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]], your character is tied to an NFT so you can't just make infinite characters without cost.  The NFT's are like keys to the game so they should cost a lot in either money or effort or time or work to aquire and the NFT creator is responsible to make their best effort to only give one per person or just be consistent with whatever amount per person they allow. Pseudonym pairs either online [[https://www.docdroid.net/file/download/3OkttUN/online-pseudonym-parties-a-foundation-for-proof-of-personhood-in-the-web-30-jurisdiction-pdf.pdf|#]] or offline is the most responsible way to do this, or something like proof of work [[CollectBit]] [[mineable nft]] would work but something like "Governmental Identity Verification" or "KYC" should never be used as it breaks the whole point of decentralized blockchain.%0a%3c %0a%3c In terms of can someone then bot that character while they are sleeping for example, it would be possible.  One way to counter this would be AI bot recognition blockchain analysis software.  It isn't that these NFT's would be banned if discovered as a bot, you can't remove something valid on the blockchain. But they could be labeled as potential automated accounts in competing block explorer gui's (a lot like competing browsers, some browsers mark "potentially harmful websites") and items gained by these accounts could also be labeled in gui's, so those who want to play legit could avoid them.  Also you would be able to see statistics using block explorer GUI for accounts play time and time of day and average play time per day etc to see if they trust this account.%0a%3c %0a%3c This does seem a lot like "social credit score" and it would be if this were tied to someones real life identity.  NFT's in the case of [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]] are pseudononymous uncensorable crypto like bitcoin and thus are the responsible way to use this technology as opposed to web3 which seeks to tie your real government identity to the web.  Identities are disposable on true blockchain as you can always stop using one NFT and get another to use.  If the NFT creator won't issue you another one (they should if using some type of pseudononymous pair as new identities can be gained ever certain amount of days) you can find another NFT creator's game and use that.  This blockchain will support nearly infinite cross-compatible games running simultaneously.  Anyone can create a set of NFT's to distribute for their own flavor or mod of the game.%0a%3c %0a385c377,385%0a%3c Would be a modernized version of this 40 year dnd game that has many different games running at once [[https://nerdist.com/article/dungeons-and-dragons-campaign-running-for-over-40-years/|#]] video [[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=nJ-ehbVQYxI|#]]%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a---%0a> Would be a modernized version of this 40 year dnd game that has many different games running at once [[https://nerdist.com/article/dungeons-and-dragons-campaign-running-for-over-40-years/|#]] video [[https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=nJ-ehbVQYxI|#]]%0a> %0a> !!Botting prevention%0a> %0a> Like has been partially discussed in [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]], your character is tied to an NFT so you can't just make infinite characters without cost.  The NFT's are like keys to the game so they should cost a lot in either money or effort or time or work to aquire and the NFT creator is responsible to make their best effort to only give one per person or just be consistent with whatever amount per person they allow. Pseudonym pairs either online [[https://www.docdroid.net/file/download/3OkttUN/online-pseudonym-parties-a-foundation-for-proof-of-personhood-in-the-web-30-jurisdiction-pdf.pdf|#]] or offline is the most responsible way to do this, or something like proof of work [[CollectBit]] [[mineable nft]] would work but something like "Governmental Identity Verification" or "KYC" should never be used as it breaks the whole point of decentralized blockchain.%0a> %0a> In terms of can someone then bot that character while they are sleeping for example, it would be possible.  One way to counter this would be AI bot recognition blockchain analysis software.  It isn't that these NFT's would be banned if discovered as a bot, you can't remove something valid on the blockchain. But they could be labeled as potential automated accounts in competing block explorer gui's (a lot like competing browsers, some browsers mark "potentially harmful websites") and items gained by these accounts could also be labeled in gui's, so those who want to play legit could avoid them.  Also you would be able to see statistics using block explorer GUI for accounts play time and time of day and average play time per day etc to see if they trust this account.%0a> %0a> This does seem a lot like "social credit score" and it would be if this were tied to someones real life identity.  NFT's in the case of [[NatureVault.ProofOfPlay]] are pseudononymous uncensorable crypto like bitcoin and thus are the responsible way to use this technology as opposed to web3 which seeks to tie your real government identity to the web.  Identities are disposable on true blockchain as you can always stop using one NFT and get another to use.  If the NFT creator won't issue you another one (they should if using some type of pseudononymous pair as new identities can be gained ever certain amount of days) you can find another NFT creator's game and use that.  This blockchain will support nearly infinite cross-compatible games running simultaneously.  Anyone can create a set of NFT's to distribute for their own flavor or mod of the game.%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
